    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Big-Theta Notation Explained</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n            line-height: 1.6;\n            max-width: 800px;\n            margin: 0 auto;\n            padding: 20px;\n            color: #333;\n        }\n        h1 {\n            color: #2c3e50;\n            text-align: center;\n            border-bottom: 2px solid #3498db;\n            padding-bottom: 10px;\n        }\n        .definition {\n            background-color: #f9f9f9;\n            border-left: 4px solid #3498db;\n            padding: 10px 15px;\n            margin: 20px 0;\n        }\n        .example {\n            background-color: #e8f4fc;\n            border: 1px solid #b3d9ff;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            padding: 15px;\n            margin: 15px 0;\n            overflow-x: auto;\n        }\n        code {\n            background-color: #f0f0f0;\n            padding: 2px 4px;\n            border-radius: 3px;\n            font-family: monospace;\n        }\n        button {\n            background-color: #3498db;\n            color: white;\n            border: none;\n            padding: 8px 15px;\n            border-radius: 4px;\n            cursor: pointer;\n            margin: 10px 0;\n        }\n        button:hover {\n            background-color: #2980b9;\n        }\n        #output {\n            background-color: #f0f0f0;\n            padding: 10px;\n            border-radius: 4px;\n            font-family: monospace;\n            min-height: 100px;\n        }\n        .visualization {\n            margin: 20px 0;\n            text-align: center;\n        }\n        .graph {\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 300px;\n            background-color: #f7f7f7;\n            border: 1px solid #ddd;\n            margin: 10px 0;\n            position: relative;\n        }\n        .bar {\n            position: absolute;\n            bottom: 0;\n            background-color: #3498db;\n            transition: height 0.5s;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <h1>Big-Theta (Θ) Notation Explained</h1>\n    \n    <div class=\"definition\">\n        <h2>What is Big-Theta Notation?</h2>\n        <p>\n            Big-Theta notation (Θ) describes the <strong>tight bound</strong> of an algorithm's growth rate. \n            It means the algorithm's running time grows at the <strong>same rate</strong> as the function inside the Θ.\n        </p>\n        <p>\n            Formally, we say that f(n) = Θ(g(n)) if there exist positive constants c₁, c₂, and n₀ such that:\n            <br>\n            <code>0 ≤ c₁·g(n) ≤ f(n) ≤ c₂·g(n)</code> for all <code>n ≥ n₀</code>\n        </p>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"example\">\n        <h2>Example: Linear Search</h2>\n        <p>Let's analyze the linear search algorithm:</p>\n        <pre><code>function linearSearch(arr, target) {\n    for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {\n        if (arr[i] === target) return i;\n    }\n    return -1;\n}</code></pre>\n\n        <p>\n            In the <strong>best case</strong>, the target is the first element (Θ(1)).<br>\n            In the <strong>worst case</strong>, the target isn't in the array (Θ(n)).<br>\n            But Big-Theta describes the <strong>exact bound</strong> when best and worst cases are the same.\n        </p>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"example\">\n        <h2>Demonstration: Finding Θ for a Function</h2>\n        <p>Let's analyze the function: <code>f(n) = 3n² + 2n + 1</code></p>\n        <p>We can show this is Θ(n²) because:</p>\n        <ul>\n            <li>Upper bound (O): 3n² + 2n + 1 ≤ 6n² for n ≥ 1</li>\n            <li>Lower bound (Ω): 3n² + 2n + 1 ≥ 3n² for n ≥ 0</li>\n        </ul>\n        <p>Thus, 3n² ≤ 3n² + 2n + 1 ≤ 6n² for n ≥ 1, so f(n) = Θ(n²).</p>\n\n        <button onclick=\"calculateGrowth()\">Calculate Growth Rates</button>\n        <div id=\"output\"></div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"visualization\">\n        <h2>Growth Rate Visualization</h2>\n        <p>Compare different growth rates (Θ(1), Θ(n), Θ(n²)):</p>\n        <div class=\"graph\" id=\"graph\"></div>\n        <button onclick=\"drawGraph()\">Show Growth Rates</button>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"example\">\n        <h2>Common Big-Theta Notations</h2>\n        <ul>\n            <li><strong>Θ(1)</strong>: Constant time (array access, arithmetic operations)</li>\n            <li><strong>Θ(log n)</strong>: Logarithmic time (binary search)</li>\n            <li><strong>Θ(n)</strong>: Linear time (simple search through array)</li>\n            <li><strong>Θ(n log n)</strong>: Linearithmic time (efficient sorting algorithms)</li>\n            <li><strong>Θ(n²)</strong>: Quadratic time (nested loops, bubble sort)</li>\n            <li><strong>Θ(2ⁿ)</strong>: Exponential time (recursive Fibonacci)</li>\n        </ul>\n    </div>\n\n    <script>\n        function calculateGrowth() {\n            const output = document.getElementById('output');\n            output.innerHTML = '<h3>Growth Rate Comparison</h3>';\n            \n            // Our function: 3n² + 2n + 1\n            output.innerHTML += '<p>For f(n) = 3n² + 2n + 1:</p>';\n            \n            for (let n = 1; n <= 10; n++) {\n                const fn = 3 * n * n + 2 * n + 1;\n                const lowerBound = 3 * n * n;    // c₁·g(n)\n                const upperBound = 6 * n * n;     // c₂·g(n)\n                \n                output.innerHTML += `\n                    <p>n = ${n}: \n                    ${lowerBound} ≤ ${fn} ≤ ${upperBound} → \n                    ${lowerBound <= fn && fn <= upperBound ? '✅' : '❌'}\n                    </p>\n                `;\n            }\n            \n            output.innerHTML += `\n                <p>We can see that for n ≥ 1, 3n² ≤ 3n² + 2n + 1 ≤ 6n² holds true.\n                Therefore, f(n) = Θ(n²).</p>\n            `;\n        }\n        \n        function drawGraph() {\n            const graph = document.getElementById('graph');\n            graph.innerHTML = '';\n            \n            // Define the growth rates we want to compare\n            const growthRates = [\n                { name: 'Θ(1)', color: '#2ecc71', fn: n => 1 },\n                { name: 'Θ(log n)', color: '#f1c40f', fn: n => Math.log2(n) * 10 },\n                { name: 'Θ(n)', color: '#3498db', fn: n => n * 2 },\n                { name: 'Θ(n log n)', color: '#9b59b6', fn: n => n * Math.log2(n) },\n                { name: 'Θ(n²)', color: '#e74c3c', fn: n => n * n / 5 }\n            ];\n            \n            // Create bars for each n value\n            for (let n = 1; n <= 10; n++) {\n                for (let i = 0; i < growthRates.length; i++) {\n                    const rate = growthRates[i];\n                    const height = rate.fn(n);\n                    \n                    const bar = document.createElement('div');\n                    bar.className = 'bar';\n                    bar.style.height = `${height}px`;\n                    bar.style.width = `${15}px`;\n                    bar.style.left = `${n * 60 + i * 20}px`;\n                    bar.style.backgroundColor = rate.color;\n                    bar.title = `${rate.name} at n=${n}: ${height.toFixed(1)}`;\n                    \n                    graph.appendChild(bar);\n                }\n            }\n            \n            // Add legend\n            const legend = document.createElement('div');\n            legend.style.marginTop = '10px';\n            growthRates.forEach(rate => {\n                legend.innerHTML += `\n                    <span style=\"display: inline-block; width: 20px; height: 10px; background-color: ${rate.color};\"></span>\n                    ${rate.name}&nbsp;&nbsp;\n                `;\n            });\n            graph.parentNode.insertBefore(legend, graph.nextSibling);\n        }\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
